article.linkText: Minor, Wright rally SIU Edwardsville past Little Rock 68-66 in OT
article.story: EDWARDSVILLE, Ill. -- — Damarco Minor scored 17 points and Shamar Wright hit a go-ahead 3-pointer with 15 seconds left to rally SIU Edwardsville to a 68-66 victory over Little Rock on Thursday night. Minor added seven rebounds and six assists for the Cougars (13-9, 6-3 Ohio Valley Conference). Wright scored 15 points, shooting 4 of 10 from the field and 6 for 8 from the line. Ray'Sean Taylor hit two 3-pointers and scored 11. Bradley Douglas and Khalen Robinson both scored 13 to lead he Trojans (11-11, 5-4). Douglas added eight rebounds and Robinson had five assists. Jamir Chaplin pitched in with 11 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
